\subsection*{Question 1}
What is the bound charge distribution of an infinately long uniformly
polarized equilateral triangle whose polarization is \textbf{P}.  What
is the total bound charge? What is the far field electric field
produced by the triangle?\\

\begin{center}
\includegraphics{Triangle-Dielectric.png}
\end{center}

If \textbf{P} is positive, the charges will line up to be negative on
the bottom of the triangle and the positive charges will distribute
along the upper two faces.  Half of the charge will be on the west
face, and the other half will be on the east face.


